The funeral service for veteran broadcaster Bob Mabena will take place at a crematorium West of Pretoria. JOHANNESBURG - Legendary radio personality Bob Mabena will be laid to rest on Saturday. The 51- year-old icon died from cardiac arrest this week. WATCH: Bob Mabena's body arrives home Affectionately known as The Jammer, Mabena made his mark in the industry at Radio Bop in 1989. He went on to work for several radio stations. At the time of his death, he was a presenter of Power FM's breakfast show.